	   <a name=9724015282164></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9724015282164><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>People who twink are lazy</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 24th 11:32 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Twinking is an insult to the other players.&nbsp;&nbsp;You all have this atitude that is I worked hard for my stuff, I should be allowed to do what I want with it.  Unfortuneately this is a wrong assumption.<br><br>First of all part of the fun of the game is being a newbie or lowlie and not having a full set of banded armor at lvl 1.  The fun is trying to come up a way to get it.<br><br>If you have all of the best eq at lvl 1, what are you going to do with your character?  Just lelvel?<br>If you find yourself just playing to level, you have lost the point of the game.<br><br>Secondly it isn't fair to the other players.  I have seen way to often a twinked lvl 1 character with armor way to powerful for their lvl going arround killing all of the newbie stuff in the gardens with one hit and not even looting the corpses, leaving other newly created characters no experience at all, but hey, they have a bunch of loot right?  It causes un-nessicary down time for an already slow process.<br><br>And frankly if people defend twinking so harshly without really any valid aurguments, besides its mine I can do what I want with it, that's childish and it shows that I am right.<br><br>If you feel the need to advance your newly created character, why noy have one of your high level friends sit there and buff and heal you while you take out that lvl 10 mob?  At least that puts some stratigy and dignity back to the game.<br><br>Bottom line:<br>The game wasn't meant to start off as fast as you can and to get to th highest possible level, the game was created to explore, socialize, and bassically build up a character from scratch.  It gives you a kind of pride knowing that you built up your character with a little bit of effort.<br><br>People who twink are lazy.<br><br>Eumno 25th session un-guilded Mage<br>Neinno 9th session Druid<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
